POWER BI DESKTOP: 3 Layers are there
Data layer: Local copy of data inside powerbi
Model layer
Visual Layer
IMPORT: Data is copied from the source and stored locally inside the powerbi files, then used for visuals.
Load: File connection : Files can only be imported, no other connection types are available like live connection to excel file.
Import limitation: If the source file changes, powerbi does not automatically changes data
REFRESH: This will refresh and new data will be loaded 
Import will be very fast in performance, as data is sotred in column, compressed as well.

DIRECT QUERY: Data stays in the source system and powerbi sends quries to it whenever visuals need data. Permanent request. visual layer goes to model layer to fetch data
When conecting to database, power offer 2 options. Import, DirectQuery
IMPORT mode is one way decision, you cannot later switch to directquery.
DIRECT QUERY allows switching to import later, LOAD will just import structure(metadata) to powerbi.
Limitation of directquery: In table view, you cannot preview data as data is not loaded. Many DAX functions, calculated col and modeling features are unavailable
WHY? POWERBI ONLY READS DATA, IT NEVER MANIPULATES DATA IN THE SOURCE SYSTEM
